defs.docs: A Big integer (signed version: `BigInt`, unsigned version: `BigUint`).

defs.name: Sign
defs.docs: A Sign is a `BigInt`'s composing element.

defs.name: BigInt
defs.docs: A big signed integer type.

defs.name: ToBigInt
defs.docs:
A generic trait for converting a value to a `BigInt`. This may return
 `None` when converting from `f32` or `f64`, and will always succeed
 when converting from any integer or unsigned primitive, or `BigUint`.

defs.name: to_bigint
defs.docs: Converts the value of `self` to a `BigInt`.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Creates and initializes a BigInt.

defs.name: from_biguint
defs.value: fn (mut sign: Sign, mut data: BigUint) -> BigInt
defs.docs: Creates and initializes a `BigInt`.

defs.name: from_slice
defs.docs: Creates and initializes a `BigInt`.

defs.name: assign_from_slice
defs.docs: Reinitializes a `BigInt`.

defs.name: from_bytes_be
defs.docs: Creates and initializes a `BigInt`.

defs.name: from_bytes_le
defs.docs: Creates and initializes a `BigInt`.

defs.name: from_signed_bytes_be
defs.docs:
Creates and initializes a `BigInt` from an array of bytes in
 two's complement binary representation.

defs.name: from_signed_bytes_le
defs.docs: Creates and initializes a `BigInt` from an array of bytes in two's complement.

defs.name: parse_bytes
defs.docs: Creates and initializes a `BigInt`.

defs.name: from_radix_be
defs.value: fn (sign: Sign, buf: &[u8], radix: u32) -> Option<BigInt>
defs.docs:
Creates and initializes a `BigInt`. Each u8 of the input slice is
 interpreted as one digit of the number
 and must therefore be less than `radix`.

defs.name: from_radix_le
defs.value: fn (sign: Sign, buf: &[u8], radix: u32) -> Option<BigInt>
defs.docs:
Creates and initializes a `BigInt`. Each u8 of the input slice is
 interpreted as one digit of the number
 and must therefore be less than `radix`.

defs.name: to_bytes_be
defs.docs: Returns the sign and the byte representation of the `BigInt` in big-endian byte order.

defs.name: to_bytes_le
defs.docs: Returns the sign and the byte representation of the `BigInt` in little-endian byte order.

defs.name: to_signed_bytes_be
defs.docs: Returns the two's complement byte representation of the `BigInt` in big-endian byte order.

defs.name: to_signed_bytes_le
defs.docs: Returns the two's complement byte representation of the `BigInt` in little-endian byte order.

defs.name: to_str_radix
defs.docs:
Returns the integer formatted as a string in the given radix.
 `radix` must be in the range `2...36`.

defs.name: to_radix_be
defs.docs:
Returns the integer in the requested base in big-endian digit order.
 The output is not given in a human readable alphabet but as a zero
 based u8 number.
 `radix` must be in the range `2...256`.

defs.name: to_radix_le
defs.docs:
Returns the integer in the requested base in little-endian digit order.
 The output is not given in a human readable alphabet but as a zero
 based u8 number.
 `radix` must be in the range `2...256`.

defs.name: sign
defs.docs: Returns the sign of the `BigInt` as a `Sign`.

defs.name: bits
defs.docs:
Determines the fewest bits necessary to express the `BigInt`,
 not including the sign.

defs.name: to_biguint
defs.docs: Converts this `BigInt` into a `BigUint`, if it's not negative.

defs.name: modpow
defs.docs: Returns `(self ^ exponent) mod modulus`

defs.name: sqrt
defs.docs:
Returns the truncated principal square root of `self` --
 see [Roots::sqrt](https://docs.rs/num-integer/0.1/num_integer/trait.Roots.html#method.sqrt).

defs.name: cbrt
defs.docs:
Returns the truncated principal cube root of `self` --
 see [Roots::cbrt](https://docs.rs/num-integer/0.1/num_integer/trait.Roots.html#method.cbrt).

defs.name: nth_root
defs.docs:
Returns the truncated principal `n`th root of `self` --
 See [Roots::nth_root](https://docs.rs/num-integer/0.1/num_integer/trait.Roots.html#tymethod.nth_root).
